  "prompt": "Railways SSE put under group C where all Central govt gives group B status for grade pay 4600?",
  "response": "In the Indian Railways, the status and grade pay of various positions can vary based on different classifications and organizational structures. Generally, the Senior Section Engineer (SSE) in the Indian Railways is classified under the Group C category, which corresponds to technical and operational posts.\n\nHowever, the classification and designation change can sometimes occur, particularly when considering different central government departments and their specific pay structures. The grade pay also depends on the recommendations of various pay commissions.\n\nIf there has been a recent decision or proposal to classify the SSE position in the Railways under a Group B status with a grade pay of 4600, it would require confirmation from official notifications or orders released by the Ministry of Railways or relevant authorities. \n\nFor accurate and up-to-date information, it is advisable to consult the official Railways guidelines or circulars or get in touch with the relevant department within the Indian Railways.",
